.TH STYX-ENV 1 "July 2026" "styx 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
styx-env \- show loaded environment variables and tool paths

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B styx env
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
[\fIVARIABLES...\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Show loaded environment variables and tool paths from styx.toml and styx.lock.

Displays the merged environment (global + hierarchical) that would be set when running tools or spawning a shell.

Environment includes:
.RS
.B Configured variables from [env] section in styx.toml
.B Tool paths (e.g., GOLANG_PATH, NODE_PATH)
.RE

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --export-format=FORMAT
Choose output format:
.RS
.B human (default)
Human-readable output: KEY=value, one per line.

.B shell
Shell-compatible format with proper escaping: export KEY='value'. Suitable for eval "$(styx env --export-format=shell)".

.B json
JSON format: {"KEY": "value", ...}. Suitable for programmatic use.
.RE

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Show all environment variables:
.B styx env

.TP
Show specific variable:
.B styx env RUST_BACKTRACE

.TP
Get shell-compatible output for eval:
.B eval "$(styx env --export-format=shell)"

.TP
Export to JSON for tools:
.B styx env --export-format=json | jq .GOLANG_PATH

.SH HIERARCHICAL CONFIG
Tool paths and environment variables are merged from:
.RS
1. Global config (~/.local/share/styx/styx.toml)
2. Parent directory configs (.styx/styx.toml)
3. Current directory config (.styx/styx.toml)
.RE

Child configs override parent configs for specific tools, while inheriting unspecified tools.

.SH SEE ALSO
.B styx(1)
.B styx-init(1)
.B styx-install(1)
